The paper proposes a novel approach to process anomaly correction using recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach is evaluated on a dataset of synthetic event logs, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of case-level and event-level attributes, which suggests the use of databases (cs.DB).
